{{expand Polish|date=January 2016}}
{{use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}
'''Henryk Stażewski''' (9 January 1894 – 10 June 1988) was a Polish painter, considered to be a pioneer of the classical [[avant-garde]] of the 1920s and 1930s.

Stażewski was a foremost representative of the [[Constructivism (art)|Constructivist]] movement, as well as the co-creator of the [[Geometric abstraction|Geometric Abstract]] art movement, and a member of the [[Cercle et Carré]] group of abstract painters based in Paris.

