{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}
{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}
'''Paul Webley''' [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (19 November 1953 – 2 March 2016) was director and [[vice-chancellor|principal]] of the [[School of Oriental and African Studies]], [[University of London]] from 2006 to 2015.  From 2010 until his death in 2016, he was [[Deputy Vice-Chancellor]] of the [[University of London]].<ref>SOAS Director appointed Deputy Vice-Chancellor of University of London https://www.soas.ac.uk/news/newsitem58215.html</ref>  He was a member of the editorial board of the ''[[Journal of Economic Psychology]]'' and a former president of the [[International Association for Research in Economic Psychology]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/news/former-soas-director-paul-webley-dies|title=Former SOAS director Paul Webley dies|last=|first=|date=|work=Times Higher Education (THE)|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

[[File:Webley12.JPG|thumb|alt=Paul Webley.|Paul Webley speaking at the Institute of Education.]]

Webley received his BSc and PhD from the [[London School of Economics]]. After a brief period at the [[University of Southampton]] he moved to the [[University of Exeter]], where he remained for 26 years, rising from lecturer to professor of [[economic psychology]].  He was head of the Department and School of Psychology from 1993 to 2003, and from 2003 to 2006 he was one of the university's deputy vice-chancellors (Senior Deputy VC, 2005-6).  His major research interests were economic [[socialization]], the psychology of money, and the psychology of [[tax]]ation, though he also worked on [[environmental psychology]] and the general issue of the [[social psychology]] underlying rule [[compliance (regulation)|compliance]].

Webley was appointed [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] in the [[2015 New Year Honours]] for services to higher education.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=61092|supp=y|page=N10|date=31 December 2014}}</ref><ref>[https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/391413/New_Year_Honours_List_2015.pdf 2015 New Year Honours List]</ref>

==Publications==

Webley wrote 10 books, 58 chapters in books, 68 journal articles, and more than a dozen papers for newsletters, magazines, and miscellaneous professional and academic publications. A full list is available here:
*[http://www.ex.ac.uk/%7EPWebley/publications.html Publications]

