'''''Suite for Barbara Loden''''' ([[French language|French]]: ''Supplément à la vie de Barbara Loden'') is a 2012 book by [[Nathalie Léger]]. The book was first offered in English translation by UK publishers Les Fugitives in 2015 with a translation by  Natasha Lehrer and Cécile Menon; the following year it was published in the U.S. by Dorothy, a publishing project.<ref>{{cite web|title=SUITE FOR BARBARA LODEN NATHALIE LÉGER|url=http://dorothyproject.com/?book=suite-for-barbara-loden|accessdate=30 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SUITE FOR BARBARA LODEN|url=http://www.lesfugitives.com/books/#/suite-for-barbara-loden/|accessdate=30 September 2016}}</ref>

Léger was inspired to write the piece after being asked to write an encyclopedia entry on [[Barbara Loden]]'s only film as director, the 1970 film ''[[Wanda (film)|Wanda]]''. Delving into research she found herself with enough material to write a short book, a mix of novel, biography, and art criticism.<ref>{{cite web|last1=DEMARCO|first1=AMANDA|title=SUITE FOR BARBARA LODEN BY NATHALIE LÉGER|url=http://therumpus.net/2015/06/suite-for-barbara-loden-by-nathalie-leger/|accessdate=30 September 2016}}</ref>

An excerpt from the book was published in the fall 2016 issue of ''[[The Paris Review]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Léger|first1=Nathalie|title=Barbara, Wanda|url=http://www.theparisreview.org/letters-essays/6820/barbara-wanda-nathalie-leger|accessdate=30 September 2016|work=The Paris Review}}</ref>

